explanation: This problem can be solved using dynamic programming. We maintain an array dp where dp[i] represents the number of people who know the secret at the end of day i. We initialize dp[0] to 1, as only one person knows the secret at the beginning. Then, for each day i from 1 to n, we calculate dp[i] as the sum of dp[i - 1] (the number of people who know the secret at the end of day i - 1) and dp[i - delay] (the number of people who know the secret at the end of day i - delay), minus dp[i - forget] (the number of people who forget the secret at the end of day i - forget). We take the result modulo 10^9 + 7 to avoid overflow. Finally, we return dp[n] as the number of people who know the secret at the end of day n.

